headline: Did Warren Buffett Make a Mistake When He Sold This Stock? The Company Is on the Precipice of a Monumental Achievement
summary: Warren Buffett's holding company, Berkshire Hathaway, first acquired a stake in the large U.S. bank Wells Fargo (NYSE: WFC) in 1990.  Berkshire would go on to hold the stock for another 32 years, with many market watchers often describing the relationship as a love affair.  In 2019, Berkshire began to cut its position in Wells Fargo and the large conglomerate exited the stock in 2022.
